parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To hear, listen, comprehend by hearing; pass: is heard, reported. A primary verb; to hear.
Other, another (of more than two), different. A primary word; 'else, ' i.e. Different.
From paraballo; a similitude, i.e. fictitious narrative, apothegm or adage.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Whosoever, whichsoever, whatsoever.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To plant, set. From a derivative of phuo; to set out in the earth, i.e. Implant; figuratively, to instil doctrine.
A vineyard. From ampelos; a vineyard.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To place or put around, clothe; fig: I bestow, confer. From peri and tithemi; to place around; by implication, to present.
A hedge, fence, partition. From phrasso; a fence, or inclosing barrier.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To dig, dig out, excavate. Apparently a primary verb; to 'burrow' in the ground, i.e. Dig.
A trough, vat, winepress. Apparently a primary word; a trough, i.e. Wine-vat.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From the same as oikodome; to be a house-builder, i.e. Construct or confirm.
A tower, fortified structure. Apparently a primary word; a tower or castle.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To give out, let; middle: I let out for my own advantage. From ek and didomi; to give forth, i.e. to lease.
From ge and the base of ergon; a land-worker, i.e. Farmer.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To be away from home, go into another country, be away, be abroad. From apodemos; to go abroad, i.e. Visit a foreign land.
